Hi from Queensland, Australia.
I typed in 'Good News' on Google. And was cheered up by Chris Mann's parody's. Thanks Chris.
Chin's up, to all folks around the world. Have a cry, and release...
I work in Aged Care, as a Community Care Worker, and am still able to visit clients in their homes, that Need care, and shopping.
A BIG high five to them, as US Carers cant do the usual affectinate goodbyes. But we find humour amongst, the gloves, aprons, and made to sit in the back seat of my car for appointments.! lol. It's one day at a time. Keeping my Beaut clients safe, and myself health checks before work.
AND a free Coffee/ Tea from McDonalds. Thank u Maccas.!!
Keep smiling world...
X Vick

snippet.textDisplay:
Thank You, Chris Mann. For keeping me, and I'm sure countless others, entertained with your awesome, hilarious, and most recently, moving videos during this, the most trying uncertain and scary situation many of us have ever experienced.
Being asthmatic, I'm one of those believed to be a bit "more vulnerable" to this virus. Choosing to err on the side of caution, I've been since Governor Newsom's first "stay home" order. Tedious but necessary for my (and especially my husband's) peace of mind. I'm my periodic haze of stir craziness, You've provided me many much needed and very much appreciated smiles and laughter and entertainment with your videos, humor, and remarkable talent. Also you have quickly become one of my very favorite YouTubers to watch and share with my friends and family. And I know that will continue long after this crisis is over. Yep. I'm a fan. LoL
Anyway, In the spirit of this wonderful video of yours, and right there with the many people you mention in your song, I wanted to take a minute to Thank YOU.
So, Thank you, thank you, Thank You Chris Mann. And Keep up the good work! Be safe & be well.

snippet.textDisplay: I work at an ice cream shop. Daily I have people thank me for staying open(carry out curbside only!) and providing a little bit of comfort during a critical time. We must protect and love each other. Support your local businesses, BUT be safe and smart in doing so. We don't mind being out here for you, but please respect us and what we are trying to provide in a time of need. We are all on the front line and putting ourselves at great risk. so please, just approach everything with compassion and empathy! Mind the rules. Don't get mad when I ask you to step 3 feet back. We just want everyone to be safe, happy, and healthy. #industrylife

Hi Chris and the World !
Just when I felt like breaking down, you published this song !
Iam a RN on the front line. My Husband is a Respiratory Therapist and we have a grandson who lives with us with Ewing's Sarcoma (cancer). All essential workers know they have a duty to do, even knowing their families can be affected by our caring for others. We, as essential workers are here for you! We wont stop helping others! Iam so glad you mentioned all essential workers as I have known that there is no "I" in team !
We will all get through this with God's grace!.
